.TH "follow_pfn" 9 "follow_pfn" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
follow_pfn \- look up PFN at a user virtual address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" follow_pfn
.BI "(struct vm_area_struct *vma "  ","
.BI "unsigned long address "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *pfn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vma" 12
memory mapping
.IP "address" 12
user virtual address
.IP "pfn" 12
location to store found PFN
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Only IO mappings and raw PFN mappings are allowed.

Returns zero and the pfn at \fIpfn\fP on success, -ve otherwise.
